caption:
These mambo wings are amazing, and barely take any effort to throw together! 🍗

You don’t even need to waste time combining a whole bunch of spices together for a rub – all you need are some party wings and @capitalcityco’s Sweet Hot Mambo Sauce! 😋

Mumbo (or mambo) sauce originates from DC, and it’s got this delicious flavor profile that blends spicy, sweet, and tangy, and is perfect for wings.

Here’s a lil secret: If you want to get your wings to be crispy on the outside without frying them, toss them in baking powder (NOT baking soda). Don’t expect them to come out breaded like fried chicken, but it makes the exterior a little crispier, which is a nice touch, especially if you’re making saucy wings.

👉 The full recipe is below, and visit the link in bio to get the Mambo Sauce today! 🙌 #repost #founditonamazon 
 🎥 @nomtasticfoods 
INGREDIENTS (20 wings)

20 party wings
1 tbsp baking powder (NOT baking soda!)
1/2 tsp salt
1/2 tsp pepper
1/2 cup Capital City Sweet Hot Mambo Sauce

INSTRUCTIONS: 

1️⃣ Dump the wings into a large mixing bowl, add the salt, pepper, and baking powder, and toss them all together with your hands.
2️⃣ Once you have a thin coating over all your wings, line an oven pan with foil, and place the wings on an oven-safe rack on the pan.
3️⃣ Preheat your oven to 250 degrees and put the wings in for 30 minutes.
4️⃣ After the 30 minutes is up, without taking the wings out of the oven, turn the heat up to 425 degrees and bake for another 40 minutes.
5️⃣ Then, take the wings out, and let them rest for 5 minutes.
6️⃣ Put them into another large mixing bowl (or wash the one you used before while the wings are in the oven) and toss with the Capital City Sweet Hot Mambo Sauce.
7️⃣ Dig in!
